Uttar Pradesh
Nov 06, 2014
Murder, Dowry Harassment
Description:
			A 20-year-old newly married woman was allegedly killed over dowry demand in Kuraina village under Auraiye police station area.

Satna Devi, married six months ago to Raju Bind, was allegedly poisoned to death yesterday.

The family of the woman has alleged that she was being harassed over dowry and was fed poison in the food, station officer Vinod Kumar Yadav said.

On their complaint, an FIR has been lodged against four persons including the husband, father-in-law, mother-in-law and brother-in-law. Husband and father-in-law have been arrested.

The body has been sent for post mortem examination and further investigations are on.


